as much as possible when we're outside?

240
00:15:21,797 --> 00:15:23,298
How many times do I have to tell you?

241
00:15:23,465 --> 00:15:25,801
Well then, I'm just gonna tell you.

242
00:15:26,009 --> 00:15:28,679
Cover your ears if
you don't want to hear.

243
00:15:29,638 --> 00:15:31,974
I don't have anything
against you, Light.

244
00:15:32,141 --> 00:15:33,976
I think the notebook couldn't
have been picked up

245
00:15:34,017 --> 00:15:35,686
by a better person.

246
00:15:36,145 --> 00:15:38,522
And I have to stick around with you

247
00:15:38,605 --> 00:15:41,358
until the notebook is finished
or you are.

248
00:15:41,984 --> 00:15:46,196
But, I'm not on your side or L's side.

249
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:50,200
Ryuk, I know that much already.

250
00:15:50,993 --> 00:15:53,537
That's why I'll never say
anything about

251
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:58,208
whether what you're doing is
right or wrong.

252
00:15:59,168 --> 00:16:02,713
But I'm going to say this
as your roommate.

253
00:16:03,130 --> 00:16:04,548
What's wrong, Ryuk?

254
00:16:04,715 --> 00:16:06,550
Why are you telling me
this all of a sudden?

255
00:16:07,217 --> 00:16:08,343
This isn't like you.

256
00:16:08,844 --> 00:16:11,054
I'm going to tell you this,

257
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:16,560
not because I'm an ally of Kira,
but because it's creeping me out...

258
00:16:17,186 --> 00:16:18,562
Get to the point already...

259
00:16:21,523 --> 00:16:24,610
Someone's been following
you all this time.

260
00:16:40,918 --> 00:16:43,420
He's been getting on my nerves.

261
00:16:43,712 --> 00:16:46,089
He can't see me, but...

262
00:16:47,049 --> 00:16:52,596
because I'm always hovering behind you,
I feel like I'm being watched.

263
00:16:53,430 --> 00:16:54,765
That's a problem.

264
00:16:55,349 --> 00:16:57,809
I'll get rid of him soon, Ryuk.

265
00:17:01,063 --> 00:17:02,731
<i>Just who is he?</i>

266
00:17:04,274 --> 00:17:07,444
<i>Does that mean that L has
begun to suspect the police?</i>

267
00:17:09,738 --> 00:17:13,450
<i>He must need quite a large number
of people to investigate them.</i>

268
00:17:14,076 --> 00:17:16,286
<i>Even if he had
50 people investigating...</i>

269
00:17:16,745 --> 00:17:19,790
<i>there is no chance that
I'd be suspected of being Kira.</i>

270
00:17:20,582 --> 00:17:23,835
<i>I should seem like an ordinary
high school student.</i>

271
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:27,005
<i>But, if I leave it alone
for several months,</i>

272
00:17:27,089 --> 00:17:29,800
<i>that possibility won't remain at zero.</i>

273
00:17:30,634 --> 00:17:32,803
<i>I have to learn my shadow's name.</i>

274
00:17:33,428 --> 00:17:35,681
<i>When I find that out,
I can get rid of him...</i>

275
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:38,976
Light...

276
00:17:39,935 --> 00:17:42,020
I'll let you in on something good...

277
00:17:43,230 --> 00:17:44,856
There are two big differences
between...

278
00:17:44,940 --> 00:17:48,652
Shinigami and humans
who have a Death Note.

279
00:17:49,611 --> 00:17:54,992
Do you know why Shinigami have to
write peoples' names in the Death Note?

280
00:17:55,742 --> 00:17:57,327
How would I know that?

281
00:17:58,287 --> 00:18:00,998
You're really talkative today, Ryuk.

282
00:18:01,957 --> 00:18:05,002
It's because Shinigami receive
the human's remaining life span from them.

283
00:18:06,295 --> 00:18:07,629
"Receive their remaining life span"?

284
00:18:08,088 --> 00:18:11,508
Let's say that there's a person who
will live 'til 60 in the Human World.

285
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:14,344
You write that he'll die
at forty in the Death Note.

286
00:18:15,345 --> 00:18:18,390
Sixty minus forty equals twenty.

287
00:18:18,599 --> 00:18:23,854
Those twenty years in the Human World
are added on to a Shinigami's life span.

288
00:18:25,188 --> 00:18:27,691
As long as we don't slack off,

289
00:18:27,983 --> 00:18:32,237
even if we're shot in the head
or stabbed in the heart with a knife,

290
00:18:32,321 --> 00:18:33,989
Shinigami will not die.

291
00:18:34,489 --> 00:18:38,243
But, no matter how many names
you write in the Death Note,

292
00:18:38,327 --> 00:18:40,412
your life span will not lengthen.

293
00:18:40,495 --> 00:18:44,708
That's the difference between Shinigami
and humans who have a Death Note.

294
00:18:45,542 --> 00:18:46,543
Hmm...

295
00:18:46,710 --> 00:18:49,504
To humans, that's very kind
of the Shinigami.

296
00:18:49,838 --> 00:18:51,214
That's kinda interesting.

297
00:18:52,049 --> 00:18:56,094
The second difference might even be
more interesting to you.

298
00:18:56,845 --> 00:19:00,390
Instead of lengthening life,
it's about cutting it short.

299
00:19:01,183 --> 00:19:02,517
Cutting it short?

300
00:19:04,019 --> 00:19:08,857
When a Shinigami sees a person's face,
they know their name.

301
00:19:09,358 --> 00:19:11,026
Do you know why?

302
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:13,403
A Shinigami's eyes...

303
00:19:14,529 --> 00:19:19,534
...can see a human's name and lifespan above
their heads when we look at you.

304
00:19:20,369 --> 00:19:22,245
Name. . .and lifespan?

305
00:19:23,163 --> 00:19:27,501
LIGHT YAGAMI

306
00:19:27,501 --> 00:19:27,918
I can see your name and
life span right now.

307
00:19:28,752 --> 00:19:32,255
If I convert it to human time,
I'll know how exactly how many years it is.

308
00:19:32,547 --> 00:19:35,801
Of course, I wouldn't tell you even if
you stretched my mouth open...

309
00:19:36,718 --> 00:19:39,596
Even if my mouth is
stretched out as it is.

310
00:19:42,766 --> 00:19:45,102
Shinigami never have
problems knowing

311
00:19:45,227 --> 00:19:47,396
the names of the people they kill.

312
00:19:47,771 --> 00:19:52,818
They also know how much life
they're going to receive.

313
00:19:53,527 --> 00:19:54,945
Our eyes are different.

314
00:19:55,112 --> 00:19:58,281
That's the biggest difference
between you and me.

315
00:19:59,866 --> 00:20:05,122
Shinigami can also turn the eyes
of whoever picked up their Death Note

316
00:20:05,414 --> 00:20:08,166
into Shinigami eyes.

317
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:12,754
But only if a deal is made, one that's
been with us since ancient times.

318
00:20:13,588 --> 00:20:14,631
A deal?

319
00:20:16,133 --> 00:20:18,468
The price for a Shinigami's eyes...

320
00:20:20,762 --> 00:20:24,808
is half of that human's
remaining lifetime.

321
00:20:25,642 --> 00:20:28,353
Half of my remaining lifetime...

322
00:20:28,603 --> 00:20:29,646
Yeah.

323
00:20:30,063 --> 00:20:31,022
In other words,

324
00:20:31,106 --> 00:20:34,317
if you were to live another 5O years,
you'll have 25 years left.

325
00:20:34,985 --> 00:20:36,987
If it was one year more,
you'll have half a year.

326
00:20:37,738 --> 00:20:41,491
And since you're neither
Kira's ally nor L's,

327
00:20:41,992 --> 00:20:44,202
you won't tell me the name
of someone I want to kill,

328
00:20:44,286 --> 00:20:45,454
even if you see their name.

329
00:20:46,121 --> 00:20:49,499
In other words...
I can't count on your help.

330
00:20:50,459 --> 00:20:51,626
Is that what you're trying to say?

331
00:20:51,918 --> 00:20:52,961
Yeah.

332
00:20:53,003 --> 00:20:55,881
It's also part of the Shinigami code.

333
00:20:57,132 --> 00:20:58,675
I'll say this once more.

334
00:20:59,468 --> 00:21:03,346
Give me half your remaining life
and I'll give you the Shinigami eyes.

335
00:21:04,306 --> 00:21:09,060
If I do that...
I'll know everyone's name.

336
00:21:09,978 --> 00:21:13,315
That will make it easier
to use the Death Note.

337
00:21:14,316 --> 00:21:15,358
So...

338
00:21:15,484 --> 00:21:17,652
Light, what'll it be?

339
00:21:23,784 --> 00:21:25,577
TO BE CONTINUED

340
00:21:27,496 --> 00:21:32,417
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

341
00:21:32,501 --> 00:21:37,881
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

342
00:21:38,089 --> 00:21:41,259
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

343
00:21:41,343 --> 00:21:46,890
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

344
00:21:46,932 --> 00:21:53,230
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

345
00:21:53,271 --> 00:21:57,818
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

346
00:21:58,568 --> 00:22:03,573
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

347
00:22:03,698 --> 00:22:07,160
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

348
00:22:07,244 --> 00:22:10,956
<i>To accomplish</i>

349
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:16,127
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

350
00:22:16,211 --> 00:22:21,800
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

351
00:22:21,883 --> 00:22:26,930
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

352
00:22:27,389 --> 00:22:32,519
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

353
00:22:37,107 --> 00:22:38,817
PREVIEW

354
00:22:38,817 --> 00:22:41,945
Who knew the Death Note would carry out
everything written in it so accurately?

355
00:22:41,987 --> 00:22:44,239
I DO YOU KNOW

356
00:22:44,239 --> 00:22:45,448
Exactly 11:45.

357
00:22:45,532 --> 00:22:46,950
Everything is going according to plan.

358
00:22:47,409 --> 00:22:49,119
The Death Note never fails.

359
00:22:49,369 --> 00:22:51,997
NEXT EPISODE: PURSUIT

